{"title_page": "Sarah Polonsky", "text_new": "'''Sarah Polonsky''' is a Canadian-American [[journalist]] and [[editor]] who specializes in media and [[music]].<ref name=twsVulture>Emma Rosenblum, June 25, 2010, Vulture, [http://www.vulture.com/2010/06/people_are_still_watching_the.html People Are Still Watching The Bachelor, But Why?], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...according to entertainment editor Sarah Polonsky, people have continued to tune in to the show ...\"</ref> Known as the \"global voice of dance music,\" she spearheaded and served as Chief Editor of the North American division of ''DJ Magazine.'' During her tenure there, she launched the [https://djmag.com/longreads/here-are-dj-mag-best-north-america-awards-2019-winners Best of North America Awards] as the sister event to the UK iteration, [https://djmag.com/longreads/here-are-all-dj-mag-best-british-awards-2019-winners Best of British]. She previously oversaw an electronic music magazine called ''Elektro'' as the title\u2019s managing editor.<ref>June 12, 2012, Elektro magazine, [http://elektrodaily.com/tags/sarah-polonsky/ When Ultra Met Wynn...], Retrieved March 25, 2015</ref> She was a Senior Editor of the online magazine ''[[BettyConfidential]]'' and at ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]''.<ref name=twsHReporter>Kyle Jaeger, 9/18/2013, The Hollywood Reporter, [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/aviciis-true-what-critics-are-631740 Avicii's 'True': What the Critics Are Saying], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...Vibe's Sarah Polonsky does an excellent job of capturing the critical response to Avicii's release,...\"</ref><ref name=twsSocialMedia>July 26th, 2012, Toby Daniels, Social Media Week, [http://socialmediaweek.org/conference/smw_speaker/sarah-polonsky/ SARAH POLONSKY], Retrieved , \"...Sarah Polonsky is Senior Editor at Vibe Media | Access Network. After a decade delivering pop-culture, fashion, music, celeb, health, beauty, art and lifestyle news...\"</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/vibes-senior-editor-sarah-polonsky-joins-edmbiz-2013|title=VIBE's Senior Editor Sarah Polonsky Joins EDMbiz 2013|date=7 June 2013|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=10 December 2014}}</ref><ref name=twsNYPost2>Keith J. Kelly, August 10, 2012, New York Post, [https://nypost.com/2012/08/10/luxe-startup-du-jour/ Luxe Startup Du Jour], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...Vibe is expanding beyond its hip- hop roots ... Sarah Polonsky, former managing editor of Elektro magazine, is a new senior editor....\"</ref> Polonsky was also a reporter at the ''[[National Enquirer]]'' before accepting a position at ''Page Six'' at the ''[[New York Post]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=. |first=Jessica |date=17 July 2006 |title= Sarah Polonsky Signs On as Page Six's Latest Alcoholic, May Replace a Departing Alcoholic|url= http://gawker.com/187774/sarah-polonsky-signs-on-as-page-sixs-latest-alcoholic-may-replace-a-departing-alcoholic|newspaper=[[gawker]] |location= New York, New York, USA|access-date= 22 March 2015}}</ref> The position at ''Page Six'' ended notably, when Polonsky was fired after a story in ''[[Radar Online]]'' criticized her for accepting freebies.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/gossip/jay-z-hip-hops-pond-article-1.554187|title=JAY-Z HIP-HOPS ACROSS THE POND|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|accessdate=10 December 2014}}</ref><ref name=twsNYPost>GEORGE RUSH, JOANNA RUSH, MOLLOY PATRICK, HUGUENIN CRISTINA, KINON, September 29, 2006, New York Daily News, [http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/gossip/jay-z-hip-hops-pond-article-1.554187 JAY-Z HIP-HOPS ACROSS THE POND], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...New York Post editor in chief Col Allan fired gossip writer Sarah Polonsky yesterday, ...\"</ref><ref name=twsObserver>Kat Stoeffel, 09/02/11, The Observer, [http://observer.com/2011/09/gatecrashers-subject-threw-gatecrasher-a-birthday-party-are-reporter-freebies-back/ Gatecrasher Subject Threw Gatecrasher a Birthday Party! Are Reporter Freebies Back?], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...Col Allan got wind of the situation, via Radar, he was reportedly \u201con the warpath,\u201d and fired fellow Page Sixer Sarah Polonsky fo the same day...\"</ref><ref name=twsObserver2>Choire Sicha, 10/23/06, Observer, [http://observer.com/2006/10/jared-paul-stern-is-slouching-back-with-book-lawsuit/ Jared Paul Stern Is Slouching Back With Book, Lawsuit], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...The former was Sarah Polonsky, a former National Enquirer reporter, who Radar reported on Sept. 28 had received a free massage ... terminated promptly....\"</ref><ref name=twsHG>Debbie Newman, 2007, The Hollywood Gossip,  [http://www.thehollywoodgossip.com/jossip/birthdays/happy-birthday-jossip-4-20071010/ Happy Birthday, Jossip! 38498], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...Learned how to discuss the \u201cSarah Polonsky\u201d incident without squirming uncontrollably....\"</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Polonsky, Sarah}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian magazine editors]]\n[[Category:Women magazine editors]]\n[[Category:American editors]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Sarah Polonsky''' is a Canadian-American [[journalist]] and [[editor]] who specializes in media and [[music]].<ref name=twsVulture>Emma Rosenblum, June 25, 2010, Vulture, [http://www.vulture.com/2010/06/people_are_still_watching_the.html People Are Still Watching The Bachelor, But Why?], Retrieved March 25, 2015, \"...according to entertainment editor Sarah Polonsky, people have continued to tune in to the show ...\"</ref> She currently serves as Editor of the US division of ''DJ Magazine.'' She previously oversaw an electronic music magazine called ''Elektro'' as the title\u2019s managing editor.<ref>June 12, 2012, Elektro magazine, [http://elektrodaily.com/tags/sarah-polonsky/ When Ultra Met Wynn...], Retrieved March 25, 2015</ref> She was a Senior Editor of the online magazine ''[[BettyConfidential]]