me (1927)|''Shinonome'']] (26 November 1927)\n* (No.41)/[[Japanese destroyer Usugumo (1927)|''Usugumo'']] (26 December 1927)\n* (No.42)/[[Japanese destroyer Shirakumo (1927)|''Shirakumo'']] (27 December 1927)\n* (No.43)/[[Japanese destroyer Isonami (1927)|''Isonami'']] (24 November 1927)\n* (No.44)/[[Japanese destroyer Uranami (1928)|''Uranami'']] (29 November 1928)\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.45)/[[Japanese destroyer Ayanami (1929)|''Ayanami'']] (5 October 1929)\n* (No.46)/[[Japanese destroyer Shikinami (1929)|''Shikinami'']] (22 June 1929)\n* (No.47)/[[Japanese destroyer Asagiri (1929)|''Asagiri'']] (18 November 1929)\n* (No.48)/[[Japanese destroyer Y\u016bgiri (1930)|''Y\u016bgiri'']] (12 May 1930)\n* (No.49)/[[Japanese destroyer Amagiri (1930)|''Amagiri'']] (27 February 1930)\n* (No.50)/[[Japanese destroyer Sagiri|''Sagiri'']] (23 December 1929)\n* (No.51)/[[Japanese destroyer Oboro (1930)|''Oboro'']] (8 November 1930)\n* (No.52)/[[Japanese destroyer Akebono (1930)|''Akebono'']] (7 November 1930)\n* (No.53)/[[Japanese destroyer Sazanami (1931)|''Sazanami'']] (6 June 1931)\n* (No.54)/[[Japanese destroyer Ushio (1930)|''Ushio'']] (17 November 1930)\n{{col-end}}\n====[[Akatsuki-class destroyer (1931)|''Akatsuki'' class]] \u2014 4 ships====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.55)/[[Japanese destroyer Akatsuki (1932)|''Akatsuki'']] (7 May 1932)\n* (No.56)/[[Japanese destroyer Hibiki (1932)|''Hibiki'']] (22 December 1932)\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.57)/[[Japanese destroyer Ikazuchi (1931)|''Ikazuchi'']] (22 October 1931)\n* (No.58)/[[Japanese destroyer Inazuma (1932)|''Inazuma'']] (25 February 1932)\n{{col-end}}\n===={{sclass-|Hatsuharu|destroyer|4}} \u2014 6 ships====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.59)/[[Japanese destroyer Hatsuharu (1933)|''Hatsuharu'']] (27 February 1933)\n* (No.60)/[[Japanese destroyer Nenohi (1932)|''Nenohi'']] (22 December 1932\n* (No.61)/[[Japanese destroyer Wakaba (1934)|''Wakaba'']] (18 March 1934)\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.62)/[[Japanese destroyer Hatsushimo (1933)|''Hatsushimo'']] (4 November 1933\n* (No.63)/[[Japanese destroyer Ariake (1934)|''Ariake'']] (23 September 1934)\n* (No.64)/[[Japanese destroyer Y\u016bgure (1934)|''Y\u016bgure'']] (6 May 1934)\n{{col-end}}\n===={{sclass-|Chidori|torpedo boat|4}} \u2014 4 ships====\nThese four vessels were nominally \"torpedo boats\". Built under the [[1st Naval Armaments Supplement Programme]] of 1931.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Chidori (1933)|''Chidori'']] (1 April 1933)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Manazuru (1933)|''Manazuru'']] (11 July 1933)\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Tomozuru|''Tomozuru'']] (1 October 1933)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Hatsukari|''Hatsukari'']] (19 December 1933)\n{{col-end}}\n\n===The [[Second Sino-Japanese War]] and [[World War II]]===\n===={{sclass-|\u014ctori|torpedo boat|4}} \u2014 8 ships====\nThese eight vessels were nominally \"torpedo boats\". The total of 8 excludes another 8 cancelled units.<ref>The cancelled units, Torpedo boats #13 to #20 under the 1934 Programme, were projected to have been named ''Hatsutaka'', ''Aotaka'', ''Wakataka'', ''Kumataka'', ''Yamadori'', ''Mizudori'', ''Umidori'' and ''Komadori''; however, no contracts were placed by the time the order was changed in 1937 in favour of [[CH-4-class submarine chaser|Submarine chasers #4 to #11]].</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat \u014ctori (1935)|''\u014ctori'']] (25 April 1935)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Kasasagi (1935)|''Kasasagi'']] (28 October 1935)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Hiyodori|''Hiyodori'']] (25 October 1935)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Hayabusa (1935)|''Hayabusa'']] (28 October 1935)\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Hato (1937)|''Hato'']] (25 January 1937)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Sagi (1937)|''Sagi'']] (30 January 1937)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Kari (1937)|''Kari'']] (20 January 1937)\n* [[Japanese torpedo boat Kiji (1937)|''Kiji'']] (26 January 1937)\n{{col-end}}\n\n===={{sclass-|Shiratsuyu|destroyer|4}} \u2014 10 ships====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.65)/[[Japanese destroyer Shiratsuyu (1935)|''Shiratsuyu'']] (5 April 1935)\n* (No.66)/[[Japanese destroyer Shigure (1935)|''Shigure'']] (18 May 1935)\n* (No.67)/[[Japanese destroyer Murasame (1935)|''Murasame'']] (20 June 1935) \n* (No.68)/[[Japanese destroyer Y\u016bdachi (1936)|''Y\u016bdachi'']] (21 June 1936)\n* (No.69)/[[Japanese destroyer Harusame (1935)|''Harusame'']] (21 September 1935)\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.70)/[[Japanese destroyer Samidare (1935)|''Samidare'']] (6 July 1935)\n* (No.71)/[[Japanese destroyer Umikaze (1936)|''Umikaze'']] (27 November 1936)\n* (No.72)/[[Japanese destroyer Yamakaze (1936)|''Yamakaze'']] (21 February 1936)\n* (No.73)/[[Japanese destroyer Kawakaze (1936)|''Kawakaze'']] (1 November 1936)\n* (No.74)/[[Japanese destroyer Suzukaze|''Suzukaze'']] (11 March 1937)\n{{col-end}}\n===={{sclass-|Asashio|destroyer|4}} \u2014 10 ships====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.75)/[[Japanese destroyer Asashio (1936)|''Asashio'']] (16 December 1936)\n* (No.76)/[[Japanese destroyer \u014cshio|''\u014cshio'']] (19 April 1937)\n* (No.77)/[[Japanese destroyer Michishio|''Michishio'']] (15 March 1937)\n* (No.78)/[[Japanese destroyer Arashio|''Arashio'']] (26 May 1937)\n* (No.79)/[[Japanese destroyer Yamagumo (1937)|''Yamagumo'']] (24 July 1937)\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.80)/[[Japanese destroyer Natsugumo (1937)|''Natsugumo'']] (26 May 1937)\n* (No.81)/[[Japanese destroyer Asagumo (1937)|''Asagumo'']] (5 November 1937)\n* (No.82)/[[Japanese destroyer Minegumo (1937)|''Minegumo'']] (4 November 1937)\n* (No.83)/[[Japanese destroyer Arare (1937)|''Arare'']] (16 November 1937)\n* (No.84)/[[Japanese destroyer Kasumi (1937)|''Kasumi'']] (18 November 1937)\n{{col-end}}\n===={{sclass-|Kager\u014d|destroyer|4}} (Type A) \u2014 19 ships====\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* (No.85)/[[Japanese destroyer Kager\u014d (1938)|''Kager\u014d'']] (27 September 1938)\n* (No.86)/[[Japanese destroyer Shiranui (1938)|''Shiranui'']] (28 June 1938)